<HEADLINE> Britain Strongly Urges its Citizens to Leave Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The British government Friday
strongly appealed to its citizens to leave Eritrea as soon as
possible while the border clashes between Ethiopia and Eritrea
continued worsening.
</P>
<P>
A British Foreign Office spokeswoman was quoted by Reuters as
saying Friday afternoon: "We're now strongly advising British
nationals to leave Eritrea."
</P>
<P>
"We are working closely with our European Union (EU) partners
and the Canadians and Americans to make the necessary provision
for flights out of Asmara as soon as possible," she added.
</P>
<P>
Britain, the current EU president, Thursday expressed grave
concern over the violent clashes and urged both sides to resolve
their dispute by peaceful means.  
</P>
</TEXT>
