<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Urges Clamp Down on Budget Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 5 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin Friday urged
the federal government to put a squeeze on the budget deficit,
which, he said, is the most serious problem affecting Russia.
</P>
<P>
In his weekly national radio address, Yeltsin cautioned, "We
must learn to live within our means."
</P>
<P>
The president called for the creation of an "efficient and
flexible" tax system, accompanied by an "extremely firm" policy of
taxation.
</P>
<P>
He also demanded a "serious reduction in state spending."
</P>
<P>
Part of the present economic crisis was due to Russia's
inexperience in the market economy, the president said, stressing
that Russia had to adapt to the rules of the global economy,
guaranteeing in particular long term stability for investors.
</P>
<P>
The president urged Russian people to tighten their belts in a
bid to defuse the economic crisis which is currently threatening
prices and the stability of the ruble.
</P>
<P>
Austerity, he said, was needed in all sectors of society,
including "government, industry, banking and among ordinary
citizens".
</P>
<P>
"We are responsible for our own problems," said Yeltsin. He
said the government "will not allow" price increases to occur.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
