<HEADLINE> Pakistan Resolves to Defend National Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's National Assembly
(lower house of the parliament) Friday adopted a resolution
pledging to defend national security at all costs.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, tabled by Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan,
vowed "to meet any adversity without compromising the honor and
dignity of the proud Pakistani people."
</P>
<P>
Amidst heavy pounding of desks, members of the assembly from
all the parties, across the political spectrum, urged the
international community to address the real causes of insecurity,
conflicts and tensions in South Asia "including the imperative
need of finding a just solution of the Jammu and Kashmir dispute."
</P>
<P>
While expressing the steadfastness of the Pakistani nation in
defending its national security, the resolution also reaffirmed
its total solidarity with and support for the Kashmiri cause.
</P>
</TEXT>
