<HEADLINE> UK New Car Sales Rise 1.7 pct in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- New car sales in Britain rose 1.7
percent year-on-year to 172,851 units last month, making it
possible for this year's sales to become the second highest ever
with 2.15 million units, according to figures released Friday by
the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT).
</P>
<P>
Last month's figure followed a year-on-year sales fall of more
than six percent in April and lifted sales for the first five
months of this year to 967,103, seven percent higher compared with
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The SMMT said that although Britain's surprise interest rate
rise Thursday will stem some demand in the next few months, the
key determinant of this year's sales will be the introduction of
the "S" registration plate starting from August, which is likely
to account for about one quarter of the whole year's sales.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
