<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Health Promoting Network Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The five-day regional workshop for
health education and promotion officials from English speaking
African countries ended Friday in Nyanga, east Zimbabwe, with
the formation of a health education and promotion network.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 participants representing 16 Anglophone countries
agreed that Africa needs a single and effective health education
and promotion network to focus on health related problems
affecting the continent, the Zimbabwe News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the network for Anglophone countries was done
to implement the resolution of African health ministers'
conference held in South Africa's Sun city in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
The conference resolved to have African countries cooperating
in health education and promotion matters in order to effectively
fight diseases on the continent.
</P>
<P>
It was resolved that the World Health Organization be
approached to help in the formation of another network for
Francophone countries. 
</P>
