Ethiopia's Tigray region, is "a further escalation of the war of
aggression."
</P>
<P>
"Accordingly, and in response to this Eritrean aggression,
Ethiopia has in self defense taken limited measures against
Asmara air force base," the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry did not reveal details on the air attack on
Asmara air force base, but said that "further details concerning
this matter will be made public as and when they are available."
</P>
<P>
The air attack took place after diplomats from the United
States and Rwanda just ended their mediations between Ethiopia
and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Susan Rice, U.S. Assistant Secretary of State for Africa, and
Patrick Mazimhaka, a minister in the Rwandan president's office,
had talks in Asmara with Eritrean President Isaias Afewerki.
Before arriving in Asmara, they held talks in Addis Ababa with
Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi and Ethiopia announced the
fully acceptance of the proposal of the mediators on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats of the U.S. and Rwanda had left Asmara for
Burkina Faso earlier Friday to report on the crisis to the annual
summit of the Organization of African Unity (OAU). 
