Albanians since February has escalated recently, forcing ethnic
Albanians to flee into Albania.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) reported that
between 8,000 and 10,000 refugees are now in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The influx of the refugees from Kosovo has stretched to the
limits of the food, accommodation and transportation resources in
the Tropoya area, the point of entry into Albania, according to
UNHCR.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Kosovo could top NATO agenda when NATO defense
ministers meet next week in Brussels, with all options including
the military involvement expected to be considered, NATO sources
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
