<HEADLINE> Zambia to Spend $2.2m on Polio Immunization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will spend 2.2 million U.S.
Dollars on this year's polio immunization, Health Minister Nkandu
Luo said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that this year's national polio immunization
will be conducted on July 10 and 11 as the first stage and August
7 and 8 as the second stage.
</P>
<P>
This year's target is to cover 95 percent of the country's
children who are supposed to be immunized compared with the 91
percent of last year, Nkandu Luo said.
</P>
<P>
She urged community leaders, member of parliament,
religious leaders and other civic leaders to mobilize their
communities and encourage parents to bring their children for
immunizations.
</P>
<P>
The minister also called on government ministries,
non-government organizations, industries and business houses to
support this year's national immunization days.
</P>
<P>
This year's objectives are to interrupt the transmission of
the polio virus, improve the vitamin status of the children
under five years through mass supplement, and to strengthen the
surveillance system, especially for polio, she said.
</P>
<P>
She told all parents and guardians to take all children under
five years to the immunization posts so that they can receive the
vaccine and be protected.
</P>
<P>
Luo said that the vaccine is safe and has no side effects.
</P>
