<HEADLINE> France to Boost Uganda's Milk Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The French government has embarked
on a 100,000 U.S. Dollar pilot project in Uganda to boost milk
output in the country, the French embassy here anounced.
</P>
<P>
A New Vision report said Saturday that the project,
spearheaded by an agricultural research center, is expected to
identify bottle-necks in milk production in the western district
of Mbarara.
</P>
<P>
The study will cover the counties of Nyabushozi, Kashaari and
Ibanda which jointly have a cattle population of 300,000.
</P>
<P>
Leon Letenneur, the representative of the center, said two
French experts are already in the country.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of this study which is expected to take five
months, will identify main factors that contribute to the
deterioration in quality of the milk in transit to collecting
centers.
</P>
<P>
This will be carried out under supervision of French experts
and the national agricultural research organization.
</P>
<P>
Other development programs by interested French investors in
the fields of milk production, genetic improvement and
slaughter-houses will follow when the project proves a success,
he added.  
</P>
