<HEADLINE> Zhejiang to Strengthen Environmental Protection Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Lu Wenge, deputy governor of east
China's Zhejiang Province, today called for more efforts to
protect the local environment.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the fifth provincial conference on environmental
protection, which closed today in this provincial capital, Lu
announced the target of halting the deterioration of Zhejiang's
environment by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
By that time, it is expected, industrial pollution will have
been brought under effective control, the water quality of major
rivers and lakes will have been improved, and the air quality in
major cities will be above Grade II in the state's environmental
standards, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has a population of 44 million, but has limited land
and water resources.
</P>
<P>
Only by properly coordinating the development of the economy,
the society and the environment can the province realize rapid and
healthy economic growth, Lu noted.
</P>
<P>
Over the next five years, he said, Zhejiang will carry out
three major environmental projects, focusing on purifying water,
cleaning air and planting trees, respectively, to achieve a benign
ecological circle. 
</P>
