<HEADLINE> Lithuania Beats Slovakia to play for Fifth Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania, making its debut at the
World Basketball Championship, edged Slovakia 66-58 in Saturday's
classificaion game and will compete for the fifth place of the
women's World Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Lithuanians, who were narrowly beaten by defending champion
Brazil 70-72 in Friday's quarterfinals, opened a close game as
both sides exchanged the leads 12 times and the score tied six
times before the European champion made it for good 32-31 on
Jolanta Vilutyte's basket with 2:28 left and clinched a 38-31
halftime edge.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia, fifth place finisher four years ago in Sydney,
returned from the locker room with a strong comeback, using a 14-6
run for 45:44 only sixth minutes into the second half thanks to
Zuzana Polonyova's two 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
However, Lithuania answered with a 10-1 to recapture the lead
54-46 and never at the danger situation on the way to clinching
the victory.
</P>
<P>
Center Jurgi Streimjikyte led the Lithuanians with 17 points
and 14 rebounds and Loret Berukstiene added 16. Forward Kamenikova
was the leading scorer for Slovakia with 17 points, followed by
center Anna Kotocova.
</P>
<P>
Lithuanian meets the winner between Cuba and Spain to vie for
the fifth place while Slovakia takes on the losser on Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
