<HEADLINE> Congress Censures BJP-Led Gov't for Nuke Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Senior Congress leader K.
Karunakaran Saturday charged the BJP-led government with
sacrificing national interests for the sake of its narrow
political interests in its nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
Meeting reporters at the press club in Thiruvananthapuram,
capital of Kerala State in far southwestern India, he said the
government's decision to go nuclear and subsequent handling of its
fallout have pushed the country to a dangerous phase rather than
protecting any national interests.
</P>
<P>
"Not for a single day or even over a single issue the
government has been able to create the impression that it is
working on the principle of collective responsibility," he
charged. "Things have come to such a pass that even the ruling
coalition partners have begun to stage walkouts in protest against
the government's decisions."
</P>
<P>
The government has not been able to convince the people of the
reasons for conducting the nuclear tests at this juncture, he
further said. "India had demonstrated before the world its nuclear
capability as back as 1974. One is at a loss to know what security
reasons compelled the government to go nuclear at this juncture."
</P>
<P>
He also accused the government of not having taken the
opposition into confidence before taking such a crucial decision
fraught with serious consequences. "The BJP leaders are living in
a fool's paradise if they thought that the Congress could be
scared by the nuclear bomb," he added. 
</P>
