<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Saturday called for
active international engagement in defusing the exacerbated
tension in South Asia by helping Pakistan and India find an
amicable solution to their disputes.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a weekly news briefing here late in the afternoon, a
Foreign Office spokesman said the international community should
engage itself along with Pakistan and India to find "an equitable,
just and expeditious settlement" of the Kashmir dispute.
