<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increases Science, Technology Input </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- This, China's largest economic and
financial center has significantly increased its investment into
science and technology in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Shanghai invested 15.9 billion
yuan in science and technology endeavors last year, up from 8.87
billion yuan in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of input into science and technology to the
local gross domestic product rose from 4.5 percent to 4.8 percent
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Increased input into science and technology has boosted
Shanghai's effort to introduce new and high technology. Currently,
Shanghai has 587 high-tech enterprises, with a combined output value
hitting 85 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunications sector, for example, reported 4.6
billion yuan in output value for core-business products in 1997, a
surge of 29 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, this east China metropolis has experienced a
boom in private science and technology enterprises in recent
years, with the number of such firms standing at 7,000. The firms
had a combined business income of 28 billion yuan last year, more
than four times the 1993 figure.
</P>
<P>
Overall, science and technology contributed 41 percent of
Shanghai's economic growth last year, up from 38 percent in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
