<HEADLINE> 44 Ethiopians Killed in Eritrean Air Raid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia said that 44 people
were killed and 135 wounded in the bombing of northern Ethiopian
town of Mekelle Friday by the Eritrean warplanes.
</P>
<P>
A statement, issued by Tigray State Council in Mekelle, capital
city of the state, said, "The victims of the raid on Friday were
students in school compounds and families who happened to be in
the vicinity looking for their children were also bombed in the
second raid by Eritrean warplanes."
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency Saturday quoted the statement as
saying: "The holocaust will never deter the Tigray people from
its resolve to defend the sovereignty of the country."
</P>
<P>
Eritrean warplanes have reportedly bombed Mekelle twice
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, according to a report reaching here from Asmara,
capital of Eritrea, a Ethiopian jets in turn struck twice at
Asmara military target and one Ethiopian MIG 23 was shot down
during the raid Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian warplanes bombed Eritrea's capital Asmara for a
second straight day Saturday, the report said.  
</P>
