<HEADLINE> Kurdish Rebels Kill 4 Village Guards in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK) rebels attacked late Friday night a village in Eastern
Turkey, killing four village guards, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Another six village guards and a woman were also injured in the
PKK attack on the village in Yuksekova town of Hakkari province
bordering Iran.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the ambulance which was carrying the
corpses of the slain village guards, hit a mine in the village,
and the driver was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The mine was believed to have been planted by the PKK.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war in eastern and
southeastern Turkey sine 1984. The clashes have so far claimed
over 35,000 lives. 
</P>
