<HEADLINE> French Soccer Coach Rejects Cricitism on Blues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Aime Jacquet, the French national
soccer squad manager, Saturday rejected criticism on his side,
called the Blues, after they scored a mediocre 1-0 win over
Finland on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Agence France-Presse, Jacquet said
that the Blues will prove themselves "generous, dashing, resolved
and eager to fight" in the upcoming World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the French team can win the World Cup, the coach
said, "She has all the means to answer this question."
</P>
<P>
"I am confident, calm. I am waiting for South Africa. We should
launch the World Cup."
</P>
<P>
Jacquet denied that the Blues showed a "double face" when they
played the Finns, just as they did with Belgians when they also
scored 1-0 in second half.
</P>
<P>
"All teams rely on a harsh organization. Control a game and
then impose on it needs time. Before the pause, we were often in
difficulty, especially when controlling the air ball. We later saw
a team full of the will to play and win great," he said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about his expectation of the opening match with South
Africa, he said the Blues would be careful. 
