<HEADLINE> Northern Vietnam Harvests Winter-Spring Rice Crop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Provinces in northern Vietnam has
achieved a good harvest in winter-spring rice crop dispite adverse
weather for rice farming, Vietnam News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the initial assessment of the Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, the north with more than
1,132,000 hectares of winter-spring rice is estimated to achieve
an average of per hectare yield of 4.65 tons and a total output of
5.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The harvest is about 97.43 percent of the output of the same
crop last year. The losses due to the adverse weather were
estimated at over 300,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam plans to produce 31 million tons of grain in 1998,
including 28 million tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
The north is planning to transplant summer-autumn rice on 1.26
million hectares with the hope to get a per hectare yield of 3.5
tons or a total output of 4.4 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
