<HEADLINE> Portable computer Sales Slow in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Compaq Computer will release
two new consumer notebook computers next week amid signs of
slowing sales and declining prices of portable computers in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Both coming notebooks fall above the line of 1,500 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
While notebook sales continue to outpace desktop sales, they
have not grown as fast as expected this year in the United
States. Consumers have increasingly flocked to models priced at
1,500 dollars and below.
</P>
<P>
Compaq is the number one vendor for notebooks priced between
1,500 and 2,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Now sub-1,500-dollar notebooks made up 26 percent of the retail
and mail order market in the United States.  
