Bank, the International Development Association (IDA), the Global
Environment Facility and U.N. Development Program Assistance.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean government is expected to inject another 135
million Zimbabwean Dollars (6.5 million U.S. Dollars), bringing
the total for the six-year program to 76.5 million U.S.Dollars.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Thursday, the World Bank said the
interest-free credit is made on standard IDA terms with 35 years
maturity, a 10-year grace period and a 0.75 percent service
charge.
</P>
<P>
The national park and wildlife sector improvement will benefit
tourism which is Zimbabwe's third biggest foreign currency earner
behind agriculture and mining. It is reported that number of
tourists has increased by 23 percent annually, and in 1996 alone,
the industry earned the country more than 2.7 billion 160 million
U.S. Dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
