<HEADLINE> European Union Envoys Visit Chinese Industrial Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Since June 3, ambassadors of the
European Union (EU) and 14 EU countries have been visiting
Liaoning Province, a major industrial base in northeast China, at
the invitation of the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
It is the first group visit by envoys from EU nations to one
place in China at one time, EU Ambassador Endymion Wilkinson told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"EU countries have also experienced hard years when they
renovated old industrial bases," says British Ambassador Anthony
C. Galsworthy, and "we'd like to share your happiness and
difficulties in the reforms."
</P>
<P>
According to provincial leaders, the trade between Liaoning
Province and the European Union topped 860 million US dollars
last year, 5.7 percent of the province's total foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the EU member countries had set up some 300
industrial projects in Liaoning, with a contractual investment of
1.2 billion US dollars, 5.9 percent of the province's total
contractual investment by foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The group will visit Shenyang, Fushun, Anshan and Dalian
cities in the province. 
</P>
