<HEADLINE> Pak PM Renews Talks Offer to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif on Saturday renewed his offer for talks with India to
defuse escalated tension between the two countries by solving all
the pending bilateral issues peacefully.
</P>
<P>
"Today I again invite (Indian Prime Minister) Atai Behari
Vajpayee to come forward and put an end to arms race in the
region," Sharif declared Saturday morning in a joint sitting of
the parliament, which was summoned to discuss the situation after
Pakistan went nuclear on May 28.
</P>
<P>
