<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Build Second Subway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The project to build a second
subway line in this capital of Guangdong Province has been
approved by the State Development Planning Commission, sources at
the city's Subway Corporation said.
</P>
<P>
The new south-north line involves nearly 10 billion yuan (1.2
billion US dollars) in investment, and construction work will
start this July at the site of the Haizhu Square Station. Bidding
for the clearing work is now underway.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase project covers 21.34 km, including 10.43 km of
subway, 10.03 km of elevated line, and a transitional section of
0.88 km, as well as 19 stations.
</P>
<P>
Major equipment and technologies such as automatic train
protection, automatic train operation and automatic ticketing will
be imported from abroad. In addition, platform screen doors and
other advanced metro facilities will also be used.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the finishing touches are now being put to the first
subway line, which is expected to open to traffic by the end of
this year. 
</P>
