<HEADLINE> Bulls Beat Jazz 93-88 in NBA Finals Game 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan scored 37 points
and Scottie Pippen added 21 to help the Chicago Bulls roll over
the Utah Jazz 93-88 in Game 2 of the NBA Finals in Salt Lake City
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls tied the finals score 1-1 in the best of seven
series. The next three games will be staged in the Bulls
home-court.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Pippen, who scored 13 of 15 points for the Bulls in
the first eight minutes, went on to do big in the fourth quarter,
shooting in all but two of Chicago's points.
</P>
<P>
Toni Kukoc shot all his 13 points in the first half. The
Bulls snatched 18 offensive rebounds and scored 33 points off
Utah's 20 turnovers.
</P>
<P>
Jeff Hornacek scored 20 points and Karl Malone added 16 for
Utah.
</P>
<P>
The first half ended 50-46 in favor of the Bulls, who lost the
first game 85-88 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, Pippen and Kukoc, the big three for the Bulls, scored
all the 23 points in the first quarter, and led all the way from
the very start. But in the second quarter, with Jordan off the
court, the Jazz bench displayed a superb show, beating the Bulls'
counterparts 8-0 in two minutes.
</P>
<P>
During the third quarter, the Bulls had a low 30 percentage of
shooting, while the Jazz stormed back with a 10-0 run to lead the
period 73-70.
</P>
<P>
The final quarter saw Pippen and Jordan each scored a double to
regain the lead with a 11-1 run against their rivals, who failed
to score anything with a frustrating 0-for-6 attacks.
</P>
<P>
The score seesawed from 85-81 to 88-86 until Malone missed a
mid-range shot with 23.4 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
Steve Kerr put in a pair of foul shots to enlarge the gap to
91-86 with 19.5 seconds remaining, and that settled the triumph
for the Bulls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
