<HEADLINE> Fires Cause Losses Worth 400 Million Dollars in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Fires have caused losses in forests
and crops in Nicaragua worth some 400 million U.S. dollars so far
this year, equivalent to 20 percent of the country's gross
domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Crops on some 376,000 hectares of farmland and some 526,000
hectares of forest were burned during the past five months, with
precious woods worth 142 million dollars charred.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at a symposium on grass-burning held here
this week, environmentalist Rene Escoto blamed the record drought
caused by the El Nino weather phenomenon for the fires. 
</P>
