<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FAO Stresses Sustainable Use of Natural Resources on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Rome-based United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) stressed the need for sustainable
use of the world's natural resources to mark World Environment Day
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This year's theme -- "For Life on Earth -- Save Our Seas" --
was highlighted at the ceremonies held at the FAO headquarters
here.
</P>
<P>
FAO Assistant Director-General Moritaka Hayashi, in charge of
the Fisheries Department, said: "The year 1998 has been declared
the International Year of the Ocean and the oceans are also
central to the theme of the 1998 World Environment Day, which we
are celebrating today."
</P>
<P>
He said environmental issues of fisheries were attracting more
and more attention, and called for efforts to "ensure that the
resources of the seas are utilized and managed in a sustainable,
environmentally acceptable manner" in order to support and feed
the ever-growing world population.
</P>
<P>
FAO Assistant Director-General in charge of sustainable
development Henri Carsalade said that sustainability and food
security were inseparable.
</P>
<P>
The FAO was convinced that it was "quite possible to meet the
food needs of the world, today and in the decades to come,"
because "production can be further improved while maintaining
respect for the principles of sustainable development." 
</P>
</TEXT>
