<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiamen's Re-Employment Program Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- This special economic zone of east
China's Fujian Province has reported initial success in
implementing its re-employment program.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that a total of 8,302 state-owned
enterprises workers had been laid off in Xiamen by the end of
March this year. However, 5,395 of them have been re-employed.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the smooth implementation of the re-employment
program, which was launched last July, the Xiamen municipal
government has formulated a number of rules and regulations on
re-employment and appropriated nearly 40 million yuan (4.82
million US dollars) to aid the program.
</P>
<P>
Besides financial assistance, Xiamen has also attached keen
importance to training displaced workers. By the end of last year,
a total of 7,899 laid-off workers had been trained, with the
majority having found job again.
</P>
<P>
As China's economic reform goes deeper, a considerable number
of workers have been displaced by state-owned enterprises, which
used to be significantly overstaffed and economically inefficient.
</P>
<P>
To tackle the problem of mounting unemployment, China has
launched a national re-employment program to train and divert the
laid-off workers, mainly to the service sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
