<HEADLINE> Netherlands Rout Nigeria in World Cup Warm-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Marc Overmars scored one goal and
assisted two others to pace World Cup group E seed the Netherlands
to a 5-1 victory over fellow cup finalists Nigeria in a warm-up
game on Friday in Amsterdam.
</P>
<P>
In the absence of injury-sidelined striker Dennis Bergkamp,
most of the Dutch offense was concentrated along the left flank
via Overmars and repeated efforts resulted in goals after the
Nigerians contained the hosts in the first 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Jerrel Hasselbaink connected a cross pass by Overmars for the
opener in the 32nd minute while Patrick Kluivert scored off
another Overmars cross-over in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
In the 38th minute, Overmars while dribbling fast into the
penalty area spotted a mispositioning of the Nigerian goalkeeper
who pressed too far away from his goalmouth.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch striker flopped up the ball past the keeper for a
goal of his own.
</P>
<P>
Clarence Seedorf, orchestrating Dutch offense from the opposite
flank, set Kluivert up for his second goal in the game in the 75th
minute while Pierre van Hooijdonk added a fifth two minutes later
to wind up the scoring spree.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch could have scored a couple more goals but Hasselbaink
misjudged his later shots.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria got a consolation goal in the 64th minute when Nwankwo
Kano converted a penalty kick to put the visitors on the
scoreboard as well. 
</P>
