railroad crash two days ago died in hospitals Friday evening,
bringing the latest death toll to 98, German officials said.
</P>
<P>
The InterCity Express (ICE), the country's fastest train,
derailed at 11:10 Wednesday morning near the northern German town
of Eschede and slammed into a nearby road bridge, bringing
hundreds of tons of concrete to crash down onto the middle section
of the train. (Germany-Rail Tragedy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- The German Foreign Ministry Friday pledged 1.25 million
marks (708,000 U.S. dollars) in emergency humanitarian aid for
Kosovo refugees flooding into Albania.
</P>
<P>
Among the aid, 500,000 marks (283,200 dollars) would be granted
to the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) to provide
shelters, foods and medical supplies to the Kosovo refugees in
Albania. Another 750,000 marks (424,800 dollars) would be used to
finance relief operations of the German Red Cross in the Balkan
country. (Germany-Aid-Kosovo)
</P>
