<HEADLINE> Brazil, U.S. Trade Exchanges Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Brazil-U.S. trade
reached 25.5 billion U.S. dollars last year, a growth of nearly 18
percent over 1996, the National Trade Confederation of Brazil said
Friday.
