</P>
<P>
-- Beijing will launch new green campaigns to protect the
environment of the Chinese capital. The move will also mark the
50th anniversary of the founding of New China.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The meeting of the five permanent members of the United
Nations Security Council at the foreign minister level has called
for the reduction of the tension in South Asia and the defending
of the international regime of non-proliferation through concerted
efforts. Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said that the
meeting has been "remarkably successful". 
