<DOCNO> XIE19980606.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Rebels in Sierra Leone to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of the
United Nations Friday urged all rebels in Sierra Leone to put an
end to the atrocities, cease their resistance to the authority of
the legitimate government of Sierra Leone and lay down their arms.
</P>
<P>
In its resolution unanimously adopted, the Security Council
welcomed the efforts by the government of Sierra Leone to restore
peaceful and secure conditions in the country, to re-establish
effective administration and the democratic process, and to
promote national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
The council further decided that all states shall prevent the
sale or supply, by their nationals or from their territories, or
using their flags vessels or aircraft, of arms and related
material of all types to Sierra Leone other than to the government
of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The council urged all states to prevent the entry into or
transit through their territories of leading members of the former
military junta and of the Revolutionary United Front.
</P>
<P>
The council expressed its readiness to terminate the measures
mentioned above once the control of the government of Sierra Leone
had been fully re-established over all its territory, and when all
non-governmental forces have been disarmed and demobilized.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
