<HEADLINE> Bonn Offers Humanitarian Aid for Kosovo-Albanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The German Foreign Ministry Friday
pledged 1.25 million marks (708,000 U.S. dollars) in emergency
humanitarian aid for Kosovo refugees flooding into Albania.
</P>
<P>
Among the aid, 500,000 marks (283,200 dollars) would be granted
to the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) to provide
shelters, foods and medical supplies to the Kosovo refugees in
Albania. Another 750,000 marks (424,800 dollars) would be used to
finance relief operations of the German Red Cross in the Balkan
country.
</P>
<P>
As clashes between Serb forces and pro-independence ethnic
Albanians intensified in Kosovo, a total of 11,000 refugees have
fled into northern Albania so far. 
</P>
